<h1>@Vte{{}}@HI{{shimau}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<strong>@Vte{{}}@HI{{shimau}}</strong>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<strong>@Vte{{}}@HI{{shimau}}</strong> is used to emphasize that whatever is expressed by
the verb has finished or is completed.
<p></p>

<strong>@Vte{{}}@HI{{shimatta}}</strong> is also used to indicate that something that should not
have been done was done or that something that should not have happened happened. It therefore
implies regret.
<p></p>

Whether a particular sentence using <strong>@Vte{{}}@HI{{shimatta}}</strong> is intended
to indicate completion or regret can only be determined by context.
<p></p>

